{"title_page": "Kadbanwadi, Maharashtra", "text_new": "'''Kadbanwadi''' pronounced as (Devanagari: \u0915\u0926\u092c\u0928\u0935\u093e\u0921\u0940) is a village which is based in the Indapur tehsil of Pune district in the state of Maharashtra of India. It is located at the distance of 234 Km from the state capital of Mumbai.\n\n==Milestone of Village==\nThe village was in the news because of the water conservation initiatives taken by a resident here. He is a retired teacher and resident of the village. Who have taken the degree of Bachelor\u2019s science. The efforts of this person have helped in the transformation of Kadbanwadi into a self-sufficient gram He is Pawar Bhajandas.\n\n==Agriculture==\nThis \u201cAdarsh Gram\u201d or model village is also famous for its polyhouse farming. As per the report of Agro Climatic, the village as a water scarcity zone in Maharashtra, with less than 400mm of rainfall per year. Most of the villagers used to feed shepherds and practice animal husbandry.  The forestlands have a great floral and faunal diversity.\n==Demographic==\nThe village Census Location Code Number of 2001 is 25001403188800 and Census Location Code Number of 2011 is 557049. The village is spread in the area of 2766 hectares in which total population was 1636 in which number of households were 425.\n==Geography==\nThe latitude 18.0724794 and longitude 74.8360918 are the geocoordinate of the Kadbanwadi. Marathi & Hindi are the languages used for interaction. The Pincode of the village is 413114 & the telephone code is 02111.\n\n==Nearby Villages==\nThe villages near are -\n* Thoratwadi\n* Birgundwadi\n* Shelgaon\n* Bharnewadi\n* Anthurne\n* Hangarwadi\n* Pitkeshwar\n* Sarafwadi\n* Ghorpadwadi\n* Sirsatwadi\n* Ranmodwadi\n", "text_old": "'''Kadbanwadi''' pronounced as (Devanagari: \u0915\u0926\u092c\u0928\u0935\u093e\u0921\u0940) is a village which is based in the Indapur tehsil of Pune district in the state of Maharashtra of India. It is located at the distance